  "response": "Here are some lesser-known but amazing places to visit in France:\n\n1. Provence Regions\n- Luberon villages (Gordes, Roussillon)\n- S\u00e9nanque Abbey\n- Verdon Gorge\n\n2. Brittany\n- Coastal villages like Camaret-sur-Mer\n- Megalithic sites in Carnac\n- \u00cele de Sein\n\n3. Alsace\n- Colmar\n- Riquewihr (picturesque medieval village)\n- Alsatian Wine Route\n\n4. Pyrenees Mountains\n- Cauterets\n- Cirque de Gavarnie\n- Saint-Lary-Soulan\n\n5. Dordogne\n- Sarlat-la-Can\u00e9da\n- Cave paintings in Lascaux\n- Castelnaud-la-Chapelle\n\n6. Loire Valley\n- Chenonceau Castle\n- Chinon\n- Less-crowded ch\u00e2teaux\n\n7. Corsica\n- Porto-Vecchio\n- Bonifacio\n- Calanques de Piana\n\n8. Jura Mountains\n- Cascades du H\u00e9risson\n- Ch\u00e2teau-Chalon\n- Lac de Chalain\n\nThese locations offer unique experiences away from typical tourist crowds, featuring beautiful landscapes, rich history, and authentic French culture.",
